description: The Rottweiler is a breed of domestic dog known for its medium to large size and its strength. They originate from Rottweil, Germany and are sometimes nicknamed Rottie or Rott. Although a versatile breed, used in recent times for many purposes, the Rottweiler is primarily known as one of the oldest of herding breeds. Rottweilers are a relatively healthy, disease-free breed that have been put to use in search and rescue, guide dogs and as guard or police dogs. Read all about this type of canine in our easy to read Rottweiler ebook. It will provide details about the typical size, demeanor, and common health problems associated with his type of pet.
